quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
98,8,"Their recompense lies with their Lord: Gardens of eternity beneath which rivers flow; therein they shall dwell, forever and ever. Allah is well-pleased with them, and they are well-pleased with Him. All this is for him who fears his Lord. {1}",footnotes:1:In other words
world fearlessly and independent of God, but feared Him at
every step lest he should do something which might entail
His wrath and punishment, will have this reward reserved
for him with Allah.
99,1,"When the earth will be shaken with a mighty shaking, {1}",footnotes:1:Zalzalah means to shake violently over and over again. Thus
99,2,"and the earth will throw up all her burdens, {1}",footnotes:1:This same has been expressed in Surah Al-Inshiqaq
99,3,"and man will cry out: “What is the matter with her?” {1}",footnotes:1:Man here may as well imply every man
99,4,"On that Day it will relate all her news, {1}",footnotes:1:According to Abu Hurairah
99,5,"for your Lord will have commanded her (to do so)."
99,6,"On that Day people will go forth in varying states {1} so that they be shown their deeds. {2}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings:(1) That each man will present himself in his own individual capacity. Families
99,7,"So, whoever does an atom's weight of good shall see it;"
99,8,"and whoever does an atom's weight of evil shall see it. {1}",footnotes:1:A simple and straightforward meaning of this statement
100,1,"By (the horses) that charge snorting, {1}",footnotes:1:There is no indication in the words of the verse to show whether those who run imply the horses; only the word wal-adiyat (by
100,2,"then raise sparks of fire (by their hoofs), {1}",footnotes:1:Strike sparks: indicates that the horses run in the dead of night
100,3,"then raid by the dawn, {1}",footnotes:1:The practice among the Arabs was that when they had to mount a raid on a settlement
100,4,"and blaze a trail of dust,"
100,5,"and penetrate deep into a host."
100,6,"Verily man is most ungrateful to his Lord; {1}",footnotes:1:This is for which an oath has been sworn by the horses
100,7,"and he himself is a witness to that, {1}",footnotes:1:That is his own conscience and his own deeds are a witness to it; then there are many disbelievers also who by their own tongue express their ingratitude openly
100,8,"and surely he loves riches with a passionate loving. {1}",footnotes:1:Literally He is most ardent in the love of khair. But the word khair is not only used for goodness and virtue in Arabic but also for worldly wealth. In ( Surah Al-Baqarah
100,9,"Is he not aware that when whatever lies (buried) in the graves is overthrown; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
